\subsection{H-Plane Radiation Patten of Pyramidal Horn Antenna}\label{FDTD_results_H_Plane_Horn_Pattern}\index{H-plane horn radiation pattern!FDTD}\index{FDTD!H-plane horn radiation pattern}\index{Horn radiation pattern!H-Plane}
H-plane radiation patterns of several horns are computed using FDTD technique and compared with the available measured results.


%\subsubsection{Horn-1}\label{Horn_Rudduk_H_Plane}
The radiation pattern of the first horn antenna is computed and compared with the measurement of \cite{Rudduck_hp_horn} shown in Fig.~\ref{Fig:field_h_plane_rudduk_normalished_both_color}. The FDTD predicted radiation pattern of the H-plane horn antenna is in good agreement with measured results at all angles. However, at and near $180^\circ$ FDTD results fail to predict the dip in the measurement.

\begin{figure}[tb!]
\begin{center}
\centerline{\includegraphics[scale=1.0]{field_h_plane_rudduk_normalished_both_color}}
\caption[H-plane radiation pattern of horn antenna using FDTD compared with the published measurement]{\label{Fig:field_h_plane_rudduk_normalished_both_color}H-plane radiation pattern of horn antenna using FDTD technique compared with the measured pattern of \cite{Rudduck_hp_horn}.}
\end{center}
\end{figure}

%\subsubsection{Horn-2}\label{Horn_Balanis_H_Plane}
The radiation pattern of the second horn antenna is computed and compared with the measurement of \cite{Tirkas_Contour_Path_FDTD_Pyramidal_Horns_E_Plane} shown in Fig.~\ref{Fig:field_h_plane_balanis_normalished_both_color}. The FDTD predicted radiation pattern of the H-plane horn antenna is in good agreement with measured results at all angles. 

